<paragraph id="3E5936FC2041FFC0FF2029295952BF99" blockId="21.[151,569,363,390]" box="[151,569,363,390]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading id="651181902041FFC0FF2029295952BF99" bold="true" box="[151,569,363,390]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="1">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FF2029295952BF99" bold="true" box="[151,569,363,390]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="F9E64D7F2041FFC0FF59292E5952BF99" authority="Garsault 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[238,569,363,390]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Salamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FF59292E5AE9BF9A" bold="true" box="[238,386,364,390]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Salamandra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FE3E29295952BF99" author="Garsault" box="[393,569,363,389]" firstAuthor="Garsault" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="644 - 729" refId="ref41354" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">Garsault 1764</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E5936FC2041FFC0FF2029F05A14BD66" blockId="21.[151,1436,434,890]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FF2029F05AB0BFD6" author="Dubois and Raffaelli" box="[151,475,434,458]" firstAuthor="Dubois" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref39878" refString="Dubois, A. &amp; Raffaelli, J. (2009) A new ergotaxonomy of the family Salamandridae Goldfuss, 1820 (Amphibia, Urodela). Alytes, 26, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2009">Dubois and Raffaëlli (2009)</bibRefCitation>
recently revised the taxonomy of North African 
<taxonomicName id="F9E64D7F2041FFC0FBAE29F15FC9BFD7" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[1049,1186,435,459]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Salamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FBAE29F15FC9BFD7" box="[1049,1186,435,459]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Salamandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recognized three species, one of which undescribed, and placed these in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="F9E64D7F2041FFC0FC1D29945E38BFF2" authority="Dubois and Raffaelli 2009" authorityName="Dubois and Raffaelli" authorityYear="2009" box="[938,1363,470,494]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Algiandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FC1D29945F77BFF2" box="[938,1052,470,494]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Algiandra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FB9329945E38BFF2" author="Dubois and Raffaelli" box="[1060,1363,470,494]" firstAuthor="Dubois" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref39878" refString="Dubois, A. &amp; Raffaelli, J. (2009) A new ergotaxonomy of the family Salamandridae Goldfuss, 1820 (Amphibia, Urodela). Alytes, 26, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2009">Dubois and Raffaëlli 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Their rationale for these changes depended on prior demonstrated mitochondrial divergence (
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FB0E29B85A21BC2A" author="Donaire-Barroso &amp; Bogaerts" firstAuthor="Donaire-Barroso" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="84 - 100" refId="ref39375" refString="Donaire-Barroso, D. &amp; Bogaerts, S. (2003 a) A new subspecies of Salamandra algira Bedriaga, 1883 from northern Morocco. Pod @ rcis, 4, 84 - 100." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="a">Donaire-Barroso &amp; Bogaerts 2003a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FEE12A5C5906BC2A" author="Escoriza &amp; Comas" box="[342,621,542,566]" firstAuthor="Escoriza" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="77 - 90" refId="ref40424" refString="Escoriza, D. &amp; Comas, M. M. (2007) Description of a new subspecies of Salamandra algira Bedriaga, 1883 (Amphibia: Salamandridae) from the Beni Snassen massif (Northeast Moroco). Salamandra, 43, 77 - 90." type="journal article" year="2007">Escoriza &amp; Comas 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and descriptive data on several morphological characters. However, as the supporting data for recognition of these taxa at species level is incomplete (morphology) or inconsistent (mitochondrial relations, reproductive behaviour) with current knowledge (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FBA72A245F91BC62" author="Beukema" box="[1040,1274,614,638]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Beukema" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="626 - 641" refId="ref37142" refString="Beukema, W., De Pous, P., Donaire, D., Escoriza, D., Bogaerts, S., Toxopeus, A. G., De Bie, C. A. J. M., Roca, J. &amp; Carranza, S. (2010) Biogeography and contemporary climatic differentation among Moroccan Salamandra algira. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 101, 626 - 641. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8312.2010.01506. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Beukema 
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FB362A255FD2BC62" box="[1153,1209,614,638]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, see below for details), a new rearrangement of the North African 
<taxonomicName id="F9E64D7F2041FFC0FD612AC95834BCBF" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[726,863,651,675]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Salamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FD612AC95834BCBF" box="[726,863,651,675]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Salamandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa is proposed here. Additionally, due to the fact that an extraordinary degree of adaptive, intraspecific divergence is present within the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F9E64D7F2041FFC0FABB2AEC5EFFBCDA" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[1292,1428,686,710]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Salamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FABB2AEC5EFFBCDA" box="[1292,1428,686,710]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Salamandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, morphological synapomorphic characters of proposed subgenera by 
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FC1F2A905F80BCF6" author="Dubois and Raffaelli" box="[936,1259,722,746]" firstAuthor="Dubois" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref39878" refString="Dubois, A. &amp; Raffaelli, J. (2009) A new ergotaxonomy of the family Salamandridae Goldfuss, 1820 (Amphibia, Urodela). Alytes, 26, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2009">Dubois and Raffaëlli (2009)</bibRefCitation>
are ambiguous and vary significantly even within recognized taxa. This is at least true for the proposed characters size, colour(s) and associated pattern, cranial morphology and altitudinal distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="5A774B0D2041FFC0FC762B585F2CBD2E" author="Eiselt" box="[961,1095,794,818]" firstAuthor="Eiselt" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="77 - 154" refId="ref39981" refString="Eiselt, J. (1958) Der Feuersalamander, Salamandra salamandra (L.), Beitrage zu einer taxonomischen Synthese. Abhandlungen und Berichte fur Naturkunde und Vorgeschichte Magdeburg, 10, 77 - 154." type="journal article" year="1958">Eiselt 1958</bibRefCitation>
). As recognition of subgenera within 
<taxonomicName id="F9E64D7F2041FFC0FF5D2B7C5A18BD4A" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[234,371,830,854]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Salamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C92EAEE2041FFC0FF5D2B7C5A18BD4A" box="[234,371,830,854]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Salamandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could unnecessarily complicate the already confusing systematics of the genus, we do not follow this proposal.
</paragraph>
